dc_title_s: An accurate map of Warwickshire : drawn from the best surveys and intelligence, divided into its hundreds : shewing the several roads and measured distances between town & town : also the rectories & vicarages, the parks & seats of the nobility & gentry with other useful particulars
dc_description_s: Relief shown pictorially. Includes text on the Earls and Dukes of Warwick, and the seats of nobility &c. Shows boundaries, rivers, roads, woods, parks and settlements. Decorative title cartouche. Probably issued in: The large English atlas ... / by Emanuel Bowen, ... Thomas Kitchen [sic], and others. London : printed and sold by T. Bowles, John Bowles, and Robert Sayer, [1777?]
dc_publisher_s: London : Printed for Carington Bowles ... ; John Bowles ... ; Robt. Sayer ... ; Jno. Bennett ... , 1777.
